## Error Handling Strategy
```typescript
function handleError(error: unknown): void {
  // Handle expected errors
  if (error instanceof TauriError) {
    showNotification(error.userMessage);
    return;
  }
  
  // Unexpected errors
  console.error('Critical error:', error);
  showNotification('An unexpected error occurred');
  logToMonitoringService(error);
}
```

## File Structure Convention
```text
project-root/
├── src-tauri/      # Tauri backend
├── src/            # Vue frontend
│   ├── assets/
│   ├── components/ 
│   │   ├── ui/     # Base UI components
│   │   └── app/    # App-specific components
│   ├── composables/ # Reusable logic
│   ├── layouts/
│   ├── router/
│   ├── stores/     # Pinia stores
│   ├── views/      # Page components
│   ├── App.vue
│   └── main.ts
├── index.html
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

## Critical Directives
1. **Minimal Changes**: Only modify code relevant to the current task
2. **DRY Principle**: Abstract repeated patterns into composables
3. **Type Safety**: Strict TypeScript enforcement (noImplicitAny=true)
4. **Security First**: Validate all cross-boundary communications
5. **Performance Budget**: Keep main bundle < 150KB gzipped
6. **Tauri Constraints**: Respect desktop app limitations (filesystem access, system resources)

## Documentation Standards
- JSDoc for public APIs
- Component props documentation
- Complex logic explanations
- TODO comments for known issues
- Architecture decisions in ADRs

// End of .cursorrules
